# Trivy ignore file for known false positives and accepted risks
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# zlib/minizip: integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 — Debian does not build
# the vulnerable minizip code into its zlib binary packages (Debian status: ignored)
CVE-2023-45853 exp:2026-06-30

# glibc: integer overflow in memalign — Debian bookworm marks as <no-dsa>
# (minor issue, requires attacker control of size+alignment args)
CVE-2026-0861 exp:2026-06-30

# quinn-proto Rust crate embedded in compiled Polars .so (multiqc dependency)
# No fix available until Polars releases a build with quinn-proto >= 0.11.14
CVE-2026-31812 exp:2026-06-30

# linux-pam: directory traversal (no Debian fix available as of 2026-03-14)
CVE-2025-6020 exp:2026-06-30

# GnuPG gpgv: information disclosure / potential code execution (no Debian fix available as of 2026-03-14)
CVE-2025-68973 exp:2026-06-30

# ── Go stdlib v1.23.4 in ncbi-datasets-cli 18.21.0 (ncbi_datasets container) ──
# The NCBI datasets/dataformat binaries are pre-compiled Go executables distributed
# via conda-forge. They ship Go stdlib v1.23.4; fixes require Go >= 1.24.6+.
# We cannot rebuild these — only NCBI can, by updating their Go toolchain.
# As of 2026-03-25, conda-forge ncbi-datasets-cli 18.21.0 is the latest version.
#
# Risk assessment: these binaries run in an isolated container that only downloads
# genome metadata from NCBI's API and writes local files. They do not serve TLS,
# connect to Postgres, or process untrusted archives — so the practical attack
# surface for these CVEs is minimal in our pipeline context.
#
# TODO: Remove these ignores when a newer ncbi-datasets-cli is available on
# conda-forge built with Go >= 1.24.13. Check with:
#   conda search -c conda-forge ncbi-datasets-cli
#
# crypto/tls: unexpected session resumption (CRITICAL)
CVE-2025-68121 exp:2026-06-30
# database/sql: Postgres scan race condition (HIGH)
CVE-2025-47907 exp:2026-06-30
# archive/tar: unbounded allocation parsing GNU sparse map (HIGH)
CVE-2025-58183 exp:2026-06-30
# net/url: memory exhaustion in query parameter parsing (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61726 exp:2026-06-30
# archive/zip: excessive CPU consumption building archive index (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61728 exp:2026-06-30
# crypto/x509: DoS via crafted certificate (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61729 exp:2026-06-30
# net/url: incorrect parsing of IPv6 host literals (HIGH)
CVE-2026-25679 exp:2026-06-30

# ── Debian bookworm base image: no fixes available ──
# glibc: DoS via iconv() with specific character set conversions (fix_deferred)
# Our containers don't perform attacker-controlled iconv conversions.
CVE-2026-4046 exp:2026-06-30

# ncurses: stack-based buffer overflow in infocmp CLI tool (no-dsa, low urgency)
# Our containers never invoke infocmp. Fix only in sid (6.6+).
CVE-2025-69720 exp:2026-06-30

# systemd: IPC API mishandling from unprivileged callers causing service freeze
# Our containers don't run systemd services. Fix only in sid (260.1+).
CVE-2026-29111 exp:2026-06-30
